of things. It pays to search through the sites in our rankings and reviews and read the specifications in order to find the proper NiCad (nickel-cadmium), NiMH (nickel-metal hydride), or mAh (Milliamp Hour) batteries that go with your new toy.","<b>Bodies and Paint</b><br/>Some of the sites included in our rankings and reviews provide you with direct links to manufacturer s websites so that you can best match the paint to your R/C boat. Not only can you find spray paint, bottled paint and airbrushing supplies on a number of these sites, but you will likely also find body accessories like clips, decals and body wraps.","<b>Fuel and Related Products </b><br/>Once again, the type of fuel and related accessories that are right for you will depend on the make and model of the remote control boat or boats that you own. Typically, it is recommended that you have fuel bottles, temperature guns, probes and fuel tubing on-hand.","<b>Tools</b><br/>Some of the tools   such as screwdrivers, hex wrenches and soldering equipment   you probably already have at home. Some of the others you should consider, if you haven t already, include a propeller tote bag, tools organizer and adhesive products. ","<b>Radio System Items</b> <br/>The radio system is the brains of your boat. Some of the accessories other than batteries to consider owning are the radio module compatible with your boat, related servos and a related channel receiver.","<b>Books and Software </b><br/>What we are talking about here are the books and software that go beyond the user s manual. Many of the sites included in our rankings offer how-to instructional materials, books and software on specific items like nitro motors, and basic troubleshooting guides."," There are, of course, a lot more accessories, tools and extra parts available for R/C boats. In fact, the list is almost endless, as you can see on many of the sites included in our rankings and reviews. Take some time and check them out; you might even find some items that you didn t even know you needed. ","At TopTenREVIEWS We Do the Research So You Don t Have To. <br/>"]},"id":"0430368f-f889-456d-a667-b5ad5f4d8550","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"article_page_4671","url":"/top-accessories-r-c-boat-owners-should-have","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"kevinpaul-hanson","url":"/author/kevinpaul-hanson","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"KevinPaul Hanson","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"GAGNYzuXMbAxxQeJv6TdkE","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2010-07-26T19:52:38Z","datePublished":"2010-07-26T19:52:38Z","name":"Top Accessories R/C Boat Owners Should Have","synopsis":"This article might seem to be geared toward individuals who are new to the hobby of remote control boats, and that is correct…but only partially correct.","review":{},"strapline":"This article might seem to be geared toward individuals who are new to the hobby of remote control boats, and that is correct…but only partially correct.","language":"en","dateModified":"2010-07-28T21:46:46Z","id":"9pUPKep89oxLgHW3iFKGJK","meta":{"title":"Top Accessories R/C Boat Owners Should Have","description":"Visit Top Ten Reviews to read the latest reviews and opinions. Reviews are complete with product ratings and comparisons."},"products":[],"dateImported":"2019-04-17T20:53:51Z","type":"feature","template":"standard","social":{"twitter":{"image":{"status":"","height":0,"path":"/c6RZx9txLBhqX4LfnEpz2P.jpg","checksum":"","copyright":"","fileSize":0,"width":0,"caption":"","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:53:51Z","mimeType":"","name":"4671-4671.jpg","importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/articles/4671-4671.jpg","credit":"","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:53:51Z","id":"c6RZx9txLBhqX4LfnEpz2P","dateImported":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","site":"toptenreviews","orientation":"","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/c6RZx9txLBhqX4LfnEpz2P.jpg","alt":""},"title":"Top Accessories R/C Boat Owner